  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators will conduct a randomized controlled trial comparing a telephone based
      intervention (TCM) to usual care (UC). TCM will feature a registered nurse providing a series
      of phone calls to assist caregivers in learning and modifying behavioral strategies that may
      help young children with autism to sleep better. Objective (activity monitors) and subjective
      (rating scales) data will be collected by an independent research assistant at the end of the
      project. The investigators hypothesize that TCM improves sleep duration and decreases sleep
      problems relative to a usual care control condition (UC).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
